T FACE="Verdana,Arial" SIZE=1>)<BR></FONT><BR><img src=http://www.austinpowers.com/EVIL/img/die_2.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></TD><TD VALIGN=TOP ALIGN=LEFT><B><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">verant in its eternal lameness</font></B><HR><FONT SIZE=2 FACE="Verdana,Arial">Welcome to Tuesday - Patch Day<br>
We have implemented new and exciting changes this patch. Several long standing issues have been addressed and as such if mentioned on the everquest.com boards again will result in the threads being locked or deleted and the posters will receive a warning or be banned.<br>
<br>
1. Lag<br>
<br>
As usual on patch days lag spikes will be at an all time high while the code gets &quot;broken in&quot; - deal with it.<br>
<br>
2. Epics<br>
<br>
We have implemented an end to all multiquesting on all epic quests. This will stop a player from having to pay 50K plat for a piece off a rare spawn to be multiquested. We can't stop players from paying 50K to loot the epic piece from the guild that killed the mob though we highly discourage it as it detracts from the &quot;EPIC&quot; nature of the quest.<br>
<br>
2a. VS Spawn<br>
<br>
The following changes have been implemented to give everyone a fair chance at getting the epic pieces which spawn off VS or the remains.<br>
<br>
Every VS spawn will now have a gnarled staff which will be lootable by wizards only.<br>
<br>
The VS staff will not be lootable until the followig has occured.<br>
<br>
a. All other loot must be looted off VS.<br>
b. Once a. has occured her loot every player inside Karnors will be teleported to the zoneline outside karnors.<br>
c. All wizards logged onto the servor lvl 50 and above will be ported inside karnors where a race will take place. The first one getting to the staff gets to loot it.<br>
d. Until the staff is looted no other classes will be able to zone into Karnors.<br>
<br>
VS Stones<br>
<br>
The VS remains will spawn 1 hour after the Gnarled staff is looted.<br>
<br>
Once the VS remains die the exact same procedures as outlined above for the gnarled staff will take place except rangers/druids will be involved.<br>
<br>
Since 2 stones are on the VS remains once the first stone is looted the above actions will be repeated. <br>
<br>
Since participation in the epic quests is voluntary (players are free to zone out of Karnors rather than trying to get their epic piece) no GM resses are authorized.<br>
<br>
Good hunting and good luck on the race.<br>
<br>
2b. Quillmane<br>
<br>
It was reported that this spawn was broken. We have looked into this. If you stay in SK you may have better luck (we haven't changed anything but you could still have better luck). <br>
<br>
We have also implemented the &quot;warrens trivial encounter&quot; for this spawn so if the person killing Quillmane gets no experience they will get no magic items as well. This will discourage camping the cloak by those that don't need them.<br>
<br>
2c. Palidan books<br>
<br>
Vox and Naggy will now drop a Paldian book every time she is killed. <br>
<br>
The level limit for those able to fight Vox and Naggy is now lvl 45. Lvl 46+ will be removed from the zone and during the fight and will not be able to zone back in until the dragon is looted.<br>
<br>
We hope this addresses the availability of books for these encounters.<br>
<br>
2d. Ragefire spawn<br>
<br>
Ragefire will now be a triggered spawn (rather than a spawn which shows up 1-4 days after Naggys death). His level has been changed to 70 and he will have the ability to Deathtouch 10 random people in the zone at a time. Since he is now triggerable and can appear any number of times between Naggy spawns this should alleviate guilds fighting over him.<br>
<br>
2e. Phin (Kedge)<br>
Phin will drop the quest pieces every time he is killed. However, in order to not trivialize the encounter all the seahorses in the zone will now come to his call when he is attacked no matter how far they are from him.<br>
<br>
3. Spells<br>
<br>
We have heard the call for a spell vendor to be placed in the game and we have answered. There is now a spell vendor in the game near the zone out line in Veeshan Peak. He is KOS to dragons and spawns once a month but he is there and will sell you a random spell for only 1 million plat. You may get that lvl 60 spell you are looking for or you could get the SOW spell but you do have a chance of getting any spell in the game. These are special scrolls and are no drop.<br>
<br>
4. Wizard class balance/upgrades<br>
<br>
All wizard teleport spells will now cost zero mana.<br>
<br>
5. Necro class balance/upgrades<br>
<br>
Necros will get a new spell where they can sacrifice their life for one of their group members who is about to die. The death will be nonressable. This will increase necros usefulness on big raids.<br>
<br>
6. Pathing in POH<br>
<br>
The pathing has been updated in the POH. We are not saying it is better but it has been updated.<br>
<br>
In closing we feel that we have done our utmost to address numerous player concerns in this patch and maintain the vision and game balance. Now go out there and kill something.<br>
<br>
The Verant Staff <br>
